CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 16, 1955, pg. 30, reads: "Omegas Get City Key - An Omega delegation of local fraternity brothers receives the key to the city for the fraternity's Second District Conference starting this week in Pittsburgh. Charles B. Watkins, district marshal, and Earl Brooks (second from the left), the basileus of the local Omega Psi Phi brotherhood, receive the key of welcome to the Gateway Center from Mayor David L. Lawrence. Observing the presentation in Mayor's chamber are, left to right, Frank Lavelle, local Omega's vice basileus; Brooks; Watkins; Atty. Oliver L. Johnson, former assistant district attorney; Mayor Lawrence; J.D. Lewis, district manager of North Carolina Mutual Life Insurance Company; Atty. Paul F. Jones Pittsburgh's first Negro councilman; Ronald [Roland] Sawyer, chairman of the Pittsburgh Housing Association; Ronald Pittman, the fraternity's keeper of finance, and J. Warren Watson, young Pittsburgh attorney. - Harris Photo."David L. Lawrence was Mayor of the City of Pittsburgh 1946-1959, Governor of Pennsylvania 1959-1963, and he died in 1966.
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Mayor David L. Lawrence presenting key to Omega Psi Phi fraternity, including from left: Frank Lavelle, Earl Brooks, Charles B. Watkins, Atty. Oliver L. Johnson, J. D. Lewis, Atty. Paul F. Jones, Roland Sawyer, Ronald Pittman, and J. Warren Watson, gathered in Office of the Mayor, City County Building
